{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:38:55.620578+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: d202c38a9dd8172e76072e244ad5292d61b67435)", "id": "lc_bc8cecf6-343c-4cd5-bc5c-7bc4f937e9bb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "SHELL := bash\n.ONESHELL:\n.SHELLFLAGS := -eu -o pipefail -c\n\nexport DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1\nexport COMPOSE_DOCKER_CLI_BUILD=1\n\ntargets: help\n\nup: ## Run the application\n\tdocker compose up -d --build api\n\n\ndone: check test ## Prepare for a commit\ntest: utest itest  ## Run unit and integration tests\n\nci-compose := docker compose -f .ci/docker-compose.yml\n\nutest: cleantest ## Run unit tests\n\t$(ci-compose) run --rm unit pytest -m unit .\n\nitest: cleantest ## Run integration tests\n\t$(ci-compose) run --rm integration pytest -m integration .\n\ncheck: cleantest ## Check the code base\n\t$(ci-compose) run --rm unit pre-commit run -a\n\ncleantest:  ## Clean up test containers\n\t$(ci-compose) kill\n\t$(ci-compose) down --remove-orphans\n\t$(ci-compose) build\n\n\n## Migrations\n\nmigrations: ## Generate a migration using alembic\nifeq ($(m),)\n\t@echo \"Specify a message with m={message} and a rev-id with revid={revid} (e.g. 0001 etc.)\"; exit 1\nelse ifeq ($(revid),)\n\t@echo \"Specify a message with m={message} and a rev-id with revid={revid} (e.g. 0001 etc.)\"; exit 1\nelse\n\tdocker compose run api alembic revision --autogenerate -m \"$(m)\" --rev-id=\"$(revid)\"\nendif\n\nmigrate: ## Run migrations upgrade using alembic\n\tdocker compose run --rm api alembic upgrade head\n\ndowngrade: ## Run migrations downgrade using alembic\n\tdocker compose run --rm api alembic downgrade -1\n\nhelp: ## Display this help message\n\t@awk -F '##' '/^[a-z_]+:[a-z ]+##/ { print \"\\033[34m\"$$1\"\\033[0m\" \"\\n\" $$2 }' Makefile\n", "id": "lc_f97bd625-063c-4e22-931e-b57127a45b5d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e367262d-0331-4593-bdb0-06137f909d1f", "tool_call_id": "call_03bff4629dbb4f6fb9a5001e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:39:03.047627+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've gathered enough information. Here's the answer:\n\n---\n\n## Non-Docker Setup Path\n\nThe README documents an alternative **\"Installation without Docker\"** workflow:\n\n1. **Install Poetry** (the Python dependency manager).\n2. **Create a poetry environment** by running `poetry install` at the project root.\n3. **Start the server** with a single command:\n   ```bash\n   export DB_STRING=sqlite:///test.db/\n   poetry run alembic upgrade head && poetry run uvicorn api.main:app --port 5000 --reload\n   ```\n   This runs Alembic migrations and then starts the FastAPI app on port 5000, talking to a local SQLite file (`./test.db`). The app is then available at [localhost:5000/docs](http://localhost:5000/docs).\n\n## Required Environment Variable\n\nThe database connection string variable that **must** be set is:\n\n> **`DB_STRING`**\n\nThis is consumed in `api/repository.py`:\n```python\nget_engine(os.getenv(\"DB_STRING\"))\n```\n\nIn the non-Docker workflow it's set to a SQLite URL (e.g. `sqlite:///test.db/`), while the Docker Compose setup hardcodes it to `postgresql://postgres:test@db:5432/postgres`. Either way, `DB_STRING` is the sole variable that controls which database the application connects to.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 530, "prompt_tokens": 10221, "total_tokens": 10751, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 231, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9600, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.00026222, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.00011382, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0001484}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaom